        asked them, “Let he who’s without sin throw the first stone.” 8He crouched down again and continued writing
        on the ground. 9One by one, the listeners began to leave, from the oldest, and he was left alone, the
        woman being right in front. 10Jesus straightened up and told her, “Woman, where are they? No one’s condemning
        you.” 11She said, “No one, Lord.” Jesus said, “Nor do I condemn you. Go and, from now on, don’t sin anymore.”</char>
