  <chapter eid="JHN 11" />
  <!--   **********   -->
  <!--   Chapter 12   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="12" style="c" sid="JHN 12" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JHN 12:1" />Six days before the Passover, Jesus went to Bethany, where Lazarus was, whom he, Jesus, raised from the
        dead, <verse eid="JHN 12:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="JHN 12:2" />so they held a dinner for him there; Martha was doing the serving, but Lazarus was one of the ones relaxing
        at the table<char style="sup">[a]</char> with him. <verse eid="JHN 12:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="JHN 12:3" />Then Mary takes a can’s worth<char style="sup">[b]</char> of fragrant ointment<char style="sup">[c]</char>—the
        pure, genuine expensive <char style="it">stuff—</char> poured it on his feet, and wiped his feet off
        with her hair. The house was filled with the ointment’s fragrance. <verse eid="JHN 12:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="JHN 12:4" />Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples, <char style="it">the one </char>who was going to facilitate his
        arrest, <char style="it">then </char>says, <verse eid="JHN 12:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="JHN 12:5" />”Why exactly wasn’t the ointment sold for $30,000<char style="sup">[d]</char> and <char style="it">the
        proceeds </char>donated to the poor?” <verse eid="JHN 12:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="JHN 12:6" />Now he didn’t make this remark about the poor because he gave a hoot <char style="it">about them</char>,
        but because he was a thief and, being in charge of the purse, carried the donations around non-stop.<verse eid="JHN 12:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="JHN 12:7" />So Jesus said to him, <char style="wj">“Let her be, so that she gets to commemorate the day I get embalmed</char><char
        style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JHN 12:8" /><char style="wj">The fact is, the poor always have been and always will be amongst you</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char
        style="wj">, but me you won’t always have me </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">around</char></char><char
        style="wj">.”</char><verse eid="JHN 12:8" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="JHN 12:9" />A huge crowd discovered that he was there <char style="it">in Bethany, </char>and they came <char style="it">by,
        and</char> not just because of Jesus but also so that they could catch a glimpse of Lazarus, whom he
        raised from the dead. <verse eid="JHN 12:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="JHN 12:10" />Now the chief priests determined to kill Lazarus too, <verse eid="JHN 12:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="JHN 12:11" />because, on account of him, many of the Judeans kept on departing <char style="it">from their tutelage
        </char>and believing in Jesus.<verse eid="JHN 12:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JHN 12:12" />The next day, the huge crowd which had come to the festival heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,<verse eid="JHN 12:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="JHN 12:13" />took branches off palm trees, went out to meet him, and loudly chanted over and over,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:13"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:13">Rescue us<char style="sup">[g]</char>!</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:13">Blessed is he who comes at the Lord’s behest<char style="sup">[h]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:13">The king of Israel, oh yeah!<verse eid="JHN 12:13"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="JHN 12:14" />Jesus acquired a not-yet-fully-grown donkey and mounted it, according to what’s recorded in Scripture:<verse eid="JHN 12:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="JHN 12:15" />Don’t be afraid</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:15">Fair citizens of that glorious land over the rainbow<char style="sup">[A]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:15">Take a look—your king’s coming</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:15">Mounted on a donkey colt<verse eid="JHN 12:15"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="JHN 12:16" />His disciples didn’t understand this at first, but when Jesus was glorified, they then remembered that
        these things were written in exact reference to him and that these things were done for him by them<char
        style="sup">[i]</char>.<verse eid="JHN 12:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="JHN 12:17" />So then the crowd that was with him when he summoned Lazarus from the tomb and raised him from the dead
        kept attesting <char style="it">to the miracle’s</char> validity. <verse eid="JHN 12:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JHN 12:18" />This is also the reason that the crowd converged on him: it’s because they heard that he had performed
        this miracle<char style="sup">[j]</char>. <verse eid="JHN 12:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="JHN 12:19" />So the Pharisees said amongst themselves, “As you can see, nothing we’re doing is working out<char style="sup">[k]</char>.
        Take a look—the world’s gone chasing after him to be his follower<char style="sup">[B]</char>.”<verse eid="JHN 12:19" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="JHN 12:20" />Now some of those who went down to Jerusalem to worship in the festival consisted of Greek-speaking<char
        style="it"> Jews</char><char style="sup">[C]</char>. <verse eid="JHN 12:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="JHN 12:21" />These <char style="it">people</char> approached Philip of Bethsaida, Galilee and asked him, “Sir, we’d
        like to see Jesus.” <verse eid="JHN 12:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="JHN 12:22" />Philip <char style="it">then </char>goes and speaks to Andrew, and both go and speak to Jesus. <verse eid="JHN 12:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="JHN 12:23" />Jesus’s reply is, <char style="wj">“The moment when the Man</char><char style="sup">[l]</char><char style="wj">
        will be glorified is approaching.</char><verse eid="JHN 12:23" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="JHN 12:24" /><char style="wj">”I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am—if a wheat seed doesn’t fall
        on the ground and die, it remains a single </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">wheat seed</char></char><char
        style="wj">. But if it were to die, it will bring forth a great yield. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="JHN 12:25" /><char style="wj">He whose soul, whose very life being, enjoys</char><char style="sup">[D]</char><char
        style="wj"> this world, this established order of humans, basking in the comradery and friendship that
        he receives from it, destroys it, and he who despises—indeed hates—his very life being in this world
        to the extent of life eternal, which is that special fullness of life, guards and protects it, keeping
        it from harm. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="JHN 12:26" /><char style="wj">If a given person is to serve me, let him follow me, and where I am, the one who serves
        me will be also. If a given person is to serve me, the Father will honor him, including providing his
        financial support</char><char style="sup">[E]</char><char style="wj">.</char><verse eid="JHN 12:26" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="JHN 12:27" /><char style="wj">”At this time my very life being has reached the point where it is </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">quite thoroughly </char></char><char style="wj">troubled—and what should I tell you, Father?—</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">Should I tell You to </char></char><char style="wj">rescue me from this moment
        in time?—No, on the contrary: it was for this that I arrived at this moment in time. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="JHN 12:28" /><char style="wj">Father, glorify Your reputation and everything You stand for</char><char style="sup">[m]</char><char
        style="wj">.” </char>Then a voice from heaven came forth,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:28"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:28">Having glorified <char style="it">it already, </char>I will glorify <char style="it">it </char>yet again</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:28">—I will do both, not just one or the other<verse eid="JHN 12:28"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="JHN 12:29" />So then, the crowd which was standing there listening proceeded to say that thunder had occurred, but
        others proceeded to say, “An angel has spoken to him.” <verse eid="JHN 12:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="JHN 12:30" />Jesus responded in this manner, <char style="wj">“The voice didn’t occur for my benefit, but for yours
        instead. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="JHN 12:31" /><char style="wj">Now is the moment that a verdict regarding this world, this system that the human race
        lives under, has been reached, and now is the moment that the Ruler of This System That the Human Race
        Lives Under will be </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">given the boot</char></char><char style="wj">
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">and</char></char><char style="wj"> tossed out. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="JHN 12:32" /><char style="wj">And should I be hoisted up</char><char style="sup">[F]</char><char style="wj"> off the
        ground and killed, I will rally everyone to myself.”</char><verse eid="JHN 12:32" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="JHN 12:33" />In the course of saying this, he was signifying the sort of death he would die, <char style="it">a death
        lingering over him</char>. <verse eid="JHN 12:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="JHN 12:34" />Then the crowd replied, “The Old Testament<char style="sup">[n]</char> tells us that the Messiah (the
        Christ) remains <char style="it">here on Earth </char>forever and ever, so how can you say that the Man
        must be hoisted up and killed?” <verse eid="JHN 12:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="JHN 12:35" />Jesus told them, “<char style="wj">The light will remain among you for a little while longer. Walk about
        (i.e. conduct your lives) as though you’re in possession of the light, lest the darkness take you down,
        suppressing you. He who walks about in the darkness doesn’t know where he’s going. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:35" />
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="JHN 12:36" /><char style="wj">As you’re in possession of the light, believe in the light, so that you become embodiments</char><char
        style="sup">[o]</char><char style="wj"> of light.”</char></para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 12:36">Jesus spoke these things, departed, and concealed himself from them. <verse eid="JHN 12:36"/>
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="JHN 12:37" />Though he performed so many miracles right in front of them, they <char style="it">still </char>wouldn’t
        believe in him, <verse eid="JHN 12:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="JHN 12:38" />in order that the quotation from the Prophet Isaiah would be fulfilled, in which he said,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:38"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:38">Lord, who believed our report?</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:38">And to whom has the Lord’s capabilities and actions<char style="sup">[p]</char> been revealed?<verse eid="JHN 12:38"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="JHN 12:39" />They weren’t able to believe because of what Isaiah said in addition to that,<verse eid="JHN 12:39" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="JHN 12:40" />He has blinded their eyes</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:40">And hardened their hearts</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:40">So that they won’t be able to see with their eyes</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:40">And intelligently think things through in the heart</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:40">And turn <char style="it">from their ways</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 12:40">And be healed by Me<char style="sup">[q]</char><verse eid="JHN 12:40"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="41" style="v" sid="JHN 12:41" />Isaiah said these things because he saw His glory and spoke about Him. <verse eid="JHN 12:41" />
      <verse number="42" style="v" sid="JHN 12:42" />Nevertheless, many of the rulers believed in him in spite of <char style="it">what Isaiah prophesied</char>,
        but wouldn’t profess <char style="it">their belief </char>because of the Pharisees, lest they get excommunicated.<verse eid="JHN 12:42" />
      <verse number="43" style="v" sid="JHN 12:43" />The fact is, they loved and cherished the pride and joy that mankind revels in more than the pride and
        joy which God revels in.<char style="sup">[r]</char><verse eid="JHN 12:43" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="44" style="v" sid="JHN 12:44" />Jesus cried out, <char style="wj">“He who believes in me doesn’t believe in me </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">per se </char></char><char style="wj">but instead </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">believes
        </char></char><char style="wj">in the One who sent me, </char><verse eid="JHN 12:44" />
      <verse number="45" style="v" sid="JHN 12:45" /><char style="wj">and he who beholds me beholds the One who sent me. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:45" />
      <verse number="46" style="v" sid="JHN 12:46" /><char style="wj">I—a light in the world—have come so that all who believe in me would not remain in the
        darkness. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:46" />
      <verse number="47" style="v" sid="JHN 12:47" /><char style="wj">If a given person were to hear my sayings and not guard over them for the purpose of
        adhering to them, I don’t render a verdict in his case, for I didn’t come in order to render verdicts
        over the world, all those who live according to the system which is over mankind, but instead that I
        would save the world. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:47" />
      <verse number="48" style="v" sid="JHN 12:48" /><char style="wj">He who’s not converted to my point of view and won’t whole-heartedly embrace</char><char
        style="sup">[s]</char><char style="wj"> my sayings, he has the verdict </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">in</char></char><char style="wj"> himself. The message which I spoke: that </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">will </char></char><char style="wj">render a verdict in his case on that final day when it’s
        all said and done</char><char style="sup">[t]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:48" />
      <verse number="49" style="v" sid="JHN 12:49" /><char style="wj">Because I didn’t speak from out of my own self, rather the very Father who sent me—He
        personally directed me</char><char style="sup">[u]</char><char style="wj"> as to what I would say and
        how I would talk. </char><verse eid="JHN 12:49" />
      <verse number="50" style="v" sid="JHN 12:50" /><char style="wj">And I know that His commandment is that special fullness of life, eternal life. So </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">in regard to </char></char><char style="wj">what I speak: I speak in accordance
        to the way that the Father has spoken to me.”</char><verse eid="JHN 12:50" />
    </para>
  <!--   .........   -->
