  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="13" style="c" sid="JHN 13" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JHN 13:1" />Prior to the Passover festival, Jesus had known that the time had arrived for him to depart this world
        and cross over <char style="it">back</char> <char style="it">to</char> the Father. He loved his own who
        were in the world, this established order of humans—he loved them until the very end. <verse eid="JHN 13:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="JHN 13:2" />The devil had already lodged himself in the heart of Judas <char style="it">son</char> of Simon Iscariot
        so that he would facilitate his arrest, <char style="it">while</char> a dinner was taking place; <verse eid="JHN 13:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="JHN 13:3" /><char style="it">Jesus </char>knew that the Father had placed all matters under his control<char style="sup">[a]</char>
        and<char style="it"> </char>knew<char style="it"> </char>that he <char style="it">had previously </char>departed
        from God and <char style="it">now </char>is<char style="it"> </char>heading <char style="it">back</char>
        to God. <verse eid="JHN 13:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="JHN 13:4" />Getting up from the dinner <char style="it">table, </char>he <char style="it">then </char>takes off his
        outer garments, took a towel and wrapped it around himself. <verse eid="JHN 13:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="JHN 13:5" />He <char style="it">then</char> puts some water in a wash basin and begins to wash the disciples’ feet
        and wipe them dry with the towel which was wrapped around him. <verse eid="JHN 13:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="JHN 13:6" />So he comes to Simon Peter. He <char style="it">then </char>says to him,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 13:6">“Lord, you’re going to wash my feet, <char style="it">now</char> <char style="it">are you</char>?”<verse eid="JHN 13:6"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="JHN 13:7" />Jesus’s response was, <char style="wj">“You won’t understand what I’m doing right now, but you’ll figure
        it out when everything’s all over.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:7" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JHN 13:8" />Peter <char style="it">then </char>says, “Don’t you ever wash my feet—ever.”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 13:8">Jesus answered, <char style="wj">“If I don’t </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">get to</char></char><char
        style="wj"> wash you, you can’t be a part of my inner-circle</char><char style="sup">[b]</char><char
        style="wj">.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:8"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="JHN 13:9" />Simon Peter <char style="it">then </char>tells him, “Lord, don’t just <char style="it">do</char> my feet
        but <char style="it">do</char> the hands and head too.”<verse eid="JHN 13:9" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="JHN 13:10" />Jesus <char style="it">then </char>says, <char style="wj">“He who’s been bathed doesn’t need anything
        else to be washed except for his feet; apart from that, he’s clean all over. And all of you are clean</char><char
        style="sup">[A]</char><char style="wj">…</char><char style="it"><char style="wj">actually</char></char><char
        style="wj"> no, not all of you.”</char> <verse eid="JHN 13:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="JHN 13:11" />You see, he knew the one who was facilitating his arrest; this is the reason he said that not all of
        you all are clean.<verse eid="JHN 13:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JHN 13:12" />When he’d finished washing their feet, he put his outer garments back on, sat back down <char style="it">at
        the table</char><char style="sup">[c]</char>, and told them, <char style="wj">“Do you understand what
        I’ve done? </char><verse eid="JHN 13:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="JHN 13:13" /><char style="wj">You address me as ‘Teacher’ and ‘Lord,’ and you speak properly, seeing that I am </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">Teacher and Lord</char></char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="JHN 13:14" /><char style="wj">So if I washed your feet—me, your Lord and Teacher—you too ought to wash each other’s
        feet. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="JHN 13:15" /><char style="wj">You see, I’ve left you an example so that you too would act in the same manner as I
        did. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="JHN 13:16" /><char style="wj">I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am: a servant is not superior
        to his boss, nor is an emissary</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj"> superior to the one
        who sent him. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="JHN 13:17" /><char style="wj">If you know these things, you are blessed if you would do them. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JHN 13:18" /><char style="wj">I’m not talking about all of you. I know I chose some </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">men to be my disciples</char></char><char style="wj">, but that aside, in order for the </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">verse of </char></char><char style="wj">Scripture to be fulfilled,</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 13:18"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 13:18"><char style="wj">“He who dines with me in a fellowship setting</char><char style="sup">[B]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="JHN 13:18"><char style="wj">Lifted his heel over top of me </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">to stomp on
        me</char></char><verse eid="JHN 13:18"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="JHN 13:19" /><char style="wj">”I’m telling you right now before it happens, so that you’d have faith when it does
        happen, that I am </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the One-and-Only-One</char></char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">. </char></char><verse eid="JHN 13:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="JHN 13:20" /><char style="wj">I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am: he who receives (i.e. whole-heartedly
        embraces) someone I were to send receives me. He who receives me receives the One Who sent me.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="JHN 13:21" />Having said these things, Jesus was troubled in spirit and went on record<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        to say, “I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am: one of you is going to betray me
        and facilitate my arrest.” <verse eid="JHN 13:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="JHN 13:22" />The disciples began looking at one another perplexed at what he was talking about. <verse eid="JHN 13:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="JHN 13:23" />One of his disciples, whom Jesus loved and loved, was seated next to him, and since he was a close companion
        was in physical contact with him, leaning against him<char style="sup">[C]</char>. <verse eid="JHN 13:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="JHN 13:24" />So Simon Peter nods at this fellow to ask whom he might be talking about. <verse eid="JHN 13:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="JHN 13:25" />That fellow leaned in closer to Jesus, putting his head right next to Jesus’s head<char style="sup">[C]</char>,
        and <char style="it">then </char>says to him, “Lord, who is it?” <verse eid="JHN 13:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="JHN 13:26" />Jesus replied, <char style="wj">“The one for whom I </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">ritualistically
        (signifying friendship) </char></char><char style="wj">dip a small slice</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char
        style="wj"> of bread </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">in olive oil </char></char><char style="wj">and
        give it to—that’s the guy.”</char> So he dipped the slice, takes it, and gives it to Judas <char style="it">son
        </char>of Simon Iscariot. <verse eid="JHN 13:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="JHN 13:27" />Right after giving it to him, Satan entered into<char style="sup">[D]</char> that guy. Jesus <char style="it">then
        </char>says to him, <char style="wj">“What you’re going to do, get to it—quickly now.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:27" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="JHN 13:28" />Now no one who was seated <char style="it">around the table</char> knew to what <char style="it">end
        </char>he told him this. <verse eid="JHN 13:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="JHN 13:29" />Truth be known, some of them surmised, “Since Judas is in charge of the purse, Jesus is telling him to
        go buy what we’re missing for the festival or that he should donate something to the needy.” <verse eid="JHN 13:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="JHN 13:30" />So that guy received the slice of bread and departed poste-haste; and it was night.<verse eid="JHN 13:30" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="JHN 13:31" />So when he had departed, Jesus <char style="it">then </char>says, <char style="wj">“At this time the
        Man</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj"> has been glorified, and God has been glorified
        in him, </char><verse eid="JHN 13:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="JHN 13:32" /><char style="sup">[i]</char><char style="wj"> and in him God will glorify him, and He will glorify him
        straightaway. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="JHN 13:33" /><char style="wj">Fellas</char><char style="sup">[j]</char><char style="wj">, I’ll be with you for a little
        while longer. You’ll go looking for me and just like I told the Judeans, ‘Where I’m headed, you can’t
        go’; </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">but</char></char><char style="wj"> now, I’m telling you
        as well. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="JHN 13:34" /><char style="wj">I’m giving you a brand-new directive</char><char style="sup">[k]</char><char style="wj">,
        that you would love one another</char><char style="sup">[E]</char><char style="wj">; in the same manner
        which I loved you, that you too would love each other that way. </char><verse eid="JHN 13:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="JHN 13:35" /><char style="wj">This is the means by which you’ll be recognized, understood, and known by all, since
        you are my disciples, if you were to have love for one another.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:35" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="JHN 13:36" />Simon Peter <char style="it">then </char>says to him, “Lord, where are you headed?”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 13:36">Jesus replied, <char style="wj">“Where I’m headed you can’t follow me now, but you’ll follow me </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">at some</char></char><char style="wj"> later </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">time</char></char><char style="wj">.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:36"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="JHN 13:37" />Peter <char style="it">then </char>says, “Lord, why can’t I follow you now? I’d put my life on the line<char
        style="sup">[l]</char> for you.”<verse eid="JHN 13:37" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="JHN 13:38" />Jesus <char style="it">then </char>replies, <char style="wj">“You’d put your life on the line for me?—I’m
        telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am: there’s no way whatsoever that you’ll hear a rooster
        crow until you deny me three times.”</char><verse eid="JHN 13:38" />
    </para>
