  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="14" style="c" sid="JHN 14" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JHN 14:1" /><char style="wj">”Don’t let your heart be troubled: have faith</char><char style="sup">[a]</char><char
        style="wj"> in God and have faith in me. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="JHN 14:2" /><char style="wj">On my Father’s estate</char><char style="sup">[b]</char><char style="wj"> there are
        many apartments. Now if that were not the case, I would’ve told you, because I’m going </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">over there</char></char><char style="wj"> to prepare a place for you. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="JHN 14:3" /><char style="wj">And if I manage to prepare a place for you—and I will</char><char style="sup">[A]</char><char
        style="wj">—I’ll come </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">back</char></char><char style="wj"> again
        and collect you and keep you by my side</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char style="wj">, so that
        where I am, you too will be. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="JHN 14:4" /><char style="wj">And where I’m headed, you know the way.”</char><verse eid="JHN 14:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="JHN 14:5" />Thomas <char style="it">then </char>says to him, “Lord, we don’t know where you’re headed; how can we
        know the way?” <verse eid="JHN 14:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="JHN 14:6" />Jesus <char style="it">then </char>says, <char style="wj">“I am the Way, the Truth, and the Life. No
        one can go to the Father except through me. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="JHN 14:7" /><char style="wj">If you’ve known and understood me, you will know and understand the Father too. Starting
        now, you know and understand Him and have seen Him.”</char> <verse eid="JHN 14:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JHN 14:8" />Philip <char style="it">then </char>says to him, “Lord, show us the Father this once, and that’ll be
        good enough<char style="it">.</char>” <verse eid="JHN 14:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="JHN 14:9" />Jesus <char style="it">then </char>says, <char style="wj">“I’ve been with you for such a </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">long</char></char><char style="wj"> time now, and you haven’t reached the
        point where you know and understand me, Philip? He who’s seen me has seen the Father. How can you say,
        ‘Show us the Father this once’? </char><verse eid="JHN 14:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="JHN 14:10" /><char style="wj">You don’t believe that I’m in the Father and the Father is in me, </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">do you</char></char><char style="wj">? The messages that I tell you I don’t speak from myself,
        but the Father dwelling in me does His stuff</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="JHN 14:11" /><char style="wj">Believe me: I’m in the Father and the Father is in me. If not, believe on account of
        the very works </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">which I do</char></char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JHN 14:12" /><char style="wj">I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth, I really am: he who believes in the works
        that I do—that person will do </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the same</char></char><char style="wj">—better
        even</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">—since I’m going to the Father. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="JHN 14:13" /><char style="wj">And if you happen to ask for something in particular while acting in my delegated authority</char><char
        style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj">, I will do this </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">thing</char></char><char
        style="wj">, in order that the Father would be glorified by means</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char
        style="wj"> of the Son. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="JHN 14:14" /><char style="it"><char style="wj">Let me repeat</char></char><char style="wj">—If you were to ask me
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">to do</char></char><char style="wj"> something while acting
        in my delegated authority</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj">, I will do </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">it</char></char><char style="sup">[B]</char><char style="wj">.</char><verse eid="JHN 14:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="JHN 14:15" /><char style="wj">”If you’re set on loving me</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj">, you
        would keep my commandments. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="JHN 14:16" /><char style="wj">I’ll ask the Father to give you a helper of a different kind</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char
        style="wj">, one who makes the case for you and comforts you, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">and
        He will give him </char></char><char style="wj">so that he would be with you forever, </char><verse eid="JHN 14:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="JHN 14:17" /><char style="it"><char style="wj">namely </char></char><char style="wj">the Spirit of Truth, he whom
        the world, the established order of humans, cannot get, since it doesn’t see </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">any indications </char></char><char style="wj">of him nor knows and understands him. You all
        know him, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the Spirit</char></char><char style="wj">, since he
        dwells alongside you and will be in you— </char><verse eid="JHN 14:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JHN 14:18" /><char style="it"><char style="wj">certainly,</char></char><char style="wj"> I will not have</char><char
        style="sup">[i]</char><char style="wj"> cut you loose and set you on your own as orphans—</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">certainly,</char></char><char style="wj"> I am coming to you. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="JHN 14:19" /><char style="wj">In a little while, the world will no longer see me; you see me, however, because I’m
        alive—and you too will be alive. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="JHN 14:20" /><char style="wj">In That Day you will know and understand that I am in the Father and you are in me and
        I in you. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="JHN 14:21" /><char style="wj">He who is in possession of my commandments and keeps them—that’s the person who loves
        me. He who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love him and will manifest myself to him.”</char><verse eid="JHN 14:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="JHN 14:22" />Judas (not Iscariot) <char style="it">then </char>says to him, “Lord, how has it turned out that you
        intend to manifest yourself to us and not to the world?” <verse eid="JHN 14:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="JHN 14:23" />Jesus thought it over and said, <char style="wj">“If someone were to love me, he will keep my system
        of thought, and my Father will love him, and we will come to him and form </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">and share </char></char><char style="wj">an apartment with him. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="JHN 14:24" /><char style="wj">He who doesn’t love me won’t keep my system of thought. And the system of thought you
        hear didn’t originate from me but instead is from the Father who sent me.</char><verse eid="JHN 14:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="JHN 14:25" /><char style="wj">”I have spoken these things to you while I’m still among you. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="JHN 14:26" /><char style="wj">Now the Helper, the Holy Spirit, he whom the Father will send upon my authorization</char><char
        style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj">, that person will teach you everything and remind you and cause
        you to recall all that I’ve said to you. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="JHN 14:27" /><char style="wj">I leave you peace—I give you My Peace; not in the same manner that the world, the established
        order of humans, gives you. Don’t let your heart be troubled</char><char style="sup">[j]</char><char
        style="wj"> nor cower in fear. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="JHN 14:28" /><char style="wj">You heard that I told you, ‘I’m heading out and will come to you.’ If you were consumed
        with loving me, you would rejoice </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">over this event</char></char><char
        style="wj">, because I’m going to the Father, since the Father is greater than me. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="JHN 14:29" /><char style="wj">I have spoken to you at this moment in time before it happens, so that when it happens
        you will have faith and believe. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="JHN 14:30" /><char style="wj">I don’t have a lot to talk to you about any longer; the fact is, the Ruler of the World
        (the System Which Dominates the Human Race System) is coming—and he can accuse me of nothing, tempt me
        with nothing, nor intimidate me in any way</char><char style="sup">[k]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="JHN 14:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="JHN 14:31" /><char style="wj">Anyways, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">I do what I’m going to do</char></char><char
        style="wj"> so that the world would understand that I love the Father and that I act in accordance with
        his commands.</char></para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 14:31"><char style="wj">“Get up, let’s get going.”</char><verse eid="JHN 14:31"/>
    </para>
