  <chapter number="15" style="c" sid="JHN 15" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JHN 15:1" /><char style="wj">”I am the True </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">Grape </char></char><char style="wj">Vine,
        and my Father is the gardener. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="JHN 15:2" /><char style="wj">He removes all branches that are attached to me that don’t produce</char><char style="sup">[A]</char><char
        style="wj"> any grapes</char><char style="sup">[a]</char><char style="wj">, but He prunes all</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj"> branches </char></char><char style="wj">which produce grapes and trims off
        their dead growth so that they’ll produce more. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="JHN 15:3" /><char style="wj">You’ve been pruned and trimmed already on account of the system of thought</char><char
        style="sup">[b]</char><char style="wj"> I’ve communicated to you. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="JHN 15:4" /><char style="wj">Stay attached to</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char style="wj"> me and </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">make sure </char></char><char style="wj">I</char><char style="it"><char style="wj">
        am attached </char></char><char style="wj">to you. Just as a branch can’t produce fruit on its own, except
        if it stays attached to the vine, in the same way you can’t either except if you stay attached to me.
        </char><verse eid="JHN 15:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="JHN 15:5" /><char style="wj">I’m the vine, you’re</char><char style="it"><char style="wj"> </char></char><char style="wj">the
        branch</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj">. He who stays attached to me and I to him
        produces a lot of fruit, since apart from me you can’t do a thing. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="JHN 15:6" /><char style="wj">If a given person were to not stay attached to me, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">he’ll
        be </char></char><char style="wj">like the branch that was discarded</char><char style="sup">[B]</char><char
        style="wj"> and dried out: they gather such </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">branches</char></char><char
        style="wj"> together and toss them into the </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">refuse </char></char><char
        style="wj">fire, and </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the fire </char></char><char style="wj">burns
        and burns. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="JHN 15:7" /><char style="wj">If you would stay attached</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char style="wj"> to me
        and my sayings to you, if you so-happened to want something, you’ll ask </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">for it, </char></char><char style="wj">making the request once</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">, </char></char><char style="wj">and it’ll be given to you. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JHN 15:8" /><char style="wj">My Father was glorified </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">to see to it</char></char><char
        style="wj"> that you continuously yield a lot of fruit and that you would achieve the status of being
        my disciples.</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><verse eid="JHN 15:8" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="JHN 15:9" /><char style="wj">”In the same way that the Father loved me, I love you too: dwell in My Love. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="JHN 15:10" /><char style="wj">If you were to, on the whole</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj">, keep
        my commandments, dwell in my love on the whole</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj">, just
        as I have kept my Father’s commandments and dwell in His love.</char><verse eid="JHN 15:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="JHN 15:11" /><char style="wj">”I’ve spoken these things to you so that My Joy would be in you and that your joy would
        be realized to the fullest extent. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JHN 15:12" /><char style="wj">My Commandment is this: that you love in the same way that I loved you. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="JHN 15:13" /><char style="wj">No one has a greater love than this, that he would put his life on the line</char><char
        style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj"> on behalf of his close friends. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="JHN 15:14" /><char style="wj">You all are my close friends if you do what I command you to do by way of commandment.
        </char><verse eid="JHN 15:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="JHN 15:15" /><char style="wj">No longer do I say that you are compulsory servants, since the run-of-the-mill servant
        doesn’t know what his master goes about doing, but I’ve put out the statement that you all are friends,
        because I’ve made known to you what I’ve heard from my Father and made you understand it. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="JHN 15:16" /><char style="wj">You have not chosen me, but rather I have chosen you and set you up</char><char style="sup">[i]</char><char
        style="wj"> so that you would go your own way and yield fruit and that your fruit would endure; that
        that particular thing which you were to ask the Father </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">for </char></char><char
        style="wj">while acting in my delegated authority</char><char style="sup">[j]</char><char style="wj">,
        I would give to you. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="JHN 15:17" /><char style="wj">These things I command you to do, in order that you would love one another.</char><verse eid="JHN 15:17" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JHN 15:18" /><char style="wj">”If the world, the established order of humans, hates you, understand that, first and
        foremost, it has come to hate me. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="JHN 15:19" /><char style="wj">If you were a part of</char><char style="sup">[k]</char><char style="wj"> this world-system,
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">as you went along for the ride</char></char><char style="wj">
        the world would have been cordially befriending its own, but since you’re not a part of this world-system,
        since instead I chose you </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">thereby</char></char><char style="wj">
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">taking you</char></char><char style="wj"> out of the system—because
        of this the world hates you. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="JHN 15:20" /><char style="wj">Remember the saying I told you, ‘A servant isn’t greater than his master’?—If they persecuted
        me, they’ll persecute you all too. If they followed my message, they’ll follow yours also.</char><verse eid="JHN 15:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="JHN 15:21" /><char style="wj">”Anyways, they will do all these things to you on account of my reputation and the authority
        I’ve delegated to you</char><char style="sup">[l]</char><char style="wj">, since they don’t know the
        One who sent me. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="JHN 15:22" /><char style="wj">Had I not come and spoken to them, they would not be in sin</char><char style="sup">[m]</char><char
        style="wj">. But at this time they don’t have an excuse in regard to their sin. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="JHN 15:23" /><char style="wj">He who hates me hates my Father too. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="JHN 15:24" /><char style="wj">If I had not done the </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">miraculous </char></char><char
        style="wj">works among them that no one else </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">ever </char></char><char
        style="wj">did, they wouldn’t be in sin</char><char style="sup">[m]</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char
        style="wj">. But now they have had the chance to see and observe </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">all
        that I’ve done </char></char><char style="wj">and have come to hate both me and my Father. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="JHN 15:25" /><char style="wj">That aside, that the verse from their sacred book</char><char style="sup">[n]</char><char
        style="wj"> be fulfilled, ‘They gratuitously hated me.’</char><verse eid="JHN 15:25" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="JHN 15:26" /><char style="wj">”When the Helper</char><char style="sup">[o]</char><char style="wj"> does come, whom
        I will sent to you from the Father, the Spirit of Truth, the one who proceeds forth</char><char style="sup">[p]</char><char
        style="wj"> from the Father, that </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">person</char></char><char
        style="wj"> will declare things about me for the record. </char><verse eid="JHN 15:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="JHN 15:27" /><char style="wj">And you too </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">will </char></char><char style="wj">give
        declare things about me for the record, since you’ve been with me from day-one.”</char><verse eid="JHN 15:27" />
    </para>
