  <!--   Chapter 18   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="18" style="c" sid="JHN 18" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="JHN 18:1" />After saying these things, Jesus, together with his disciples, departed to the other side of Kidron Creek,
        to where there was a garden, into which he and his disciples entered. <verse eid="JHN 18:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="JHN 18:2" />Judas, the one who’ll facilitate his arrest, was familiar with the place, since Jesus and his disciples
        had gathered there often, <verse eid="JHN 18:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="JHN 18:3" />so Judas took the platoon of soldiers <char style="it">tasked with making the arrest</char> and some
        of the high priests’ and Pharisees’ attendants and gets there with lamps, torches, and weapons. <verse eid="JHN 18:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="JHN 18:4" />Jesus, knowing everything that was about to befall him, left <char style="it">the garden </char>and <char
        style="it">then </char>says to them,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:4"><char style="wj">“Whom are you looking for?”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:4"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="JHN 18:5" />They replied, “Jesus of Nazareth.”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:5">He <char style="it">then </char>says, <char style="wj">“I am </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">he
        whom you’re looking for,</char></char><char style="wj"> </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the
        One-and-Only-One</char></char><char style="sup">[a]</char><char style="it"><char style="wj">.</char></char><char
        style="wj">”</char>
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:5">His betrayer Judas stood there among them.<verse eid="JHN 18:5"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="JHN 18:6" />As he said, <char style="wj">“I am,” </char>they thereupon retreated backwards and fell on the ground<char
        style="sup">[A]</char>. <verse eid="JHN 18:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="JHN 18:7" />So again he asked them,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:7"><char style="wj">“Whom are you looking for?”</char></para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:7">So they said, “Jesus of Nazareth.”<verse eid="JHN 18:7"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="JHN 18:8" />Jesus answered, <char style="wj">“I told you that it’s me</char><char style="sup">[b]</char><char style="wj">.
        So if I’m the one you’re looking for, let the others go their own way.” </char><verse eid="JHN 18:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="JHN 18:9" /><char style="it">He said that </char>in order that the remark, <char style="wj">“not a single one of
        them perished</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char style="wj">,” </char>would be fulfilled.<verse eid="JHN 18:9" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="JHN 18:10" />Simon Peter, in possession of a sword, hauled it out and struck the Chief Priest’s slave, slicing off
        his right ear (the name of the slave was Malchus). <verse eid="JHN 18:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="JHN 18:11" />So Jesus said to Peter, <char style="wj">“Put your sword </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">back
        </char></char><char style="wj">in its place—shall I not go through with what the Father’s assigned me
        to do</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj">?”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="JHN 18:12" />So the platoon, the captain, and the Judean attendants arrested Jesus and tied him up. <verse eid="JHN 18:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="JHN 18:13" />They went over to Annas first, as, you see, he was Caiaphas’s father-in-law, who was High Priest that
        year. <verse eid="JHN 18:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="JHN 18:14" />Now it was Caiaphas who was the one who advised the Judeans that it’s beneficial that one person die
        on behalf of the folk people.<verse eid="JHN 18:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="JHN 18:15" />Simon Peter and another disciple followed Jesus<char style="it">. </char>Now the Chief Priest’s <char
        style="it">staff</char><char style="sup">[B]</char> was familiar with that disciple, and he entered into
        the Chief Priest’s courtyard together with Jesus. <verse eid="JHN 18:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="JHN 18:16" />But Peter stood outside at the doorway. So the other disciple, the one whom the Chief Priest’s <char
        style="it">staff</char> was familiar with, spoke to the doorman and he let Peter in. <verse eid="JHN 18:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="JHN 18:17" />The doorman’s girl-servant said to Peter,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:17">“Aren’t you one of this man’s disciples too?”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:17">That fellow said, “No I’m not.”<verse eid="JHN 18:17"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="JHN 18:18" />Now the servants and attendants made a charcoal fire and were standing there keeping warm. It was cold,
        you see. Peter was standing there with them keeping warm too.<verse eid="JHN 18:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="JHN 18:19" />The Chief Priest asked Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching. <verse eid="JHN 18:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="JHN 18:20" />Jesus answered, <char style="wj">“I have spoken to the world publicly and in the open. I taught in synagogues
        and in the temple, where every Judean assembles, all the time and have said nothing that was not disclosed
        to the public. </char><verse eid="JHN 18:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="JHN 18:21" /><char style="wj">Why are you asking me? Go ask the audience what I spoke to them. Check it out </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">yourself</char></char><char style="wj">—those folks know what I told them.”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="JHN 18:22" />After he said these things, one of the attendants who was standing there slapped Jesus in the face and
        said, “Is this any way to address the High Priest?” <verse eid="JHN 18:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="JHN 18:23" />Jesus replied, <char style="wj">“If I’ve said something that’s wrong</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char
        style="wj">, for the record specify what </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">I said that </char></char><char
        style="wj">was wrong. But if </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">what I’ve said is</char></char><char
        style="wj"> correct</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">, why are you hitting me?”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="JHN 18:24" />Annas sent him tied up to the High Priest Caiaphas.<verse eid="JHN 18:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="JHN 18:25" />Now Simon Peter was standing there keeping warm. They said to him, “You’re one of his disciples too,
        aren’t you?” That guy put out a denial and said, “No I’m not.” <verse eid="JHN 18:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="JHN 18:26" />One of the high priest’s servants, a relative of the one Peter cut the ear off, <char style="it">then
        </char>says, “Didn’t I see you in the garden with him?” <verse eid="JHN 18:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="JHN 18:27" />Again Peter denied it, and without delay a rooster crowed.<verse eid="JHN 18:27" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="JHN 18:28" />They took Jesus away, <char style="it">taking him </char>from Caiaphas to the governor’s palace complex.
        Now it was early morning <char style="it">the next day</char>, and they didn’t enter the palace complex,
        so that they wouldn’t be defiled <char style="it">by having contact with Gentiles </char>but instead
        could partake of the Passover meal. <verse eid="JHN 18:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="JHN 18:29" />So Pilate <char style="it">left the complex and </char>went outside to them, and they conversed:</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:29">“What charge do you bring against this man?”<verse eid="JHN 18:29"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="JHN 18:30" />Mustering a response, they told him, “If this guy hadn’t done anything wrong, we wouldn’t have brought
        him to you.”<verse eid="JHN 18:30" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="JHN 18:31" />So Pilate told them, “Take him and prosecute him according to your code of law.”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:31">The Judeans told him, “It’s forbidden for us to sentence anyone to death.” <verse eid="JHN 18:31"/>
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="JHN 18:32" /><char style="it">The transferring of the sentencing to the Romans happened </char>in order that Jesus’s
        statement which he made be fulfilled, in which he indicated what kind of death he was going to die. <verse eid="JHN 18:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="JHN 18:33" />So Pilate went back into the complex, called for Jesus, and told him,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:33">“Are you the king of the Jews?”<verse eid="JHN 18:33"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="JHN 18:34" />Jesus replied, <char style="wj">“Are you saying this of your own accord or </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">repeating what </char></char><char style="wj">others told you about me?”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:34" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="JHN 18:35" />Pilate replied, “I’m not a Jew, now, am I? Your own people and the high priests have handed you over
        to me. What have you done?”<verse eid="JHN 18:35" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="JHN 18:36" />Jesus answered, <char style="wj">“My Kingdom is not of this world. Had My Kingdom been of this world,
        my entourage would have put up a fight so that I wouldn’t have been taken into custody by the Judeans.
        But at the present time My Kingdom is not </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">over </char></char><char
        style="wj">the place we’re at now.”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:36" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="JHN 18:37" />So Pilate said to him, “So you’re not a king?”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:37">Jesus replied, <char style="wj">“Whatever you say</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj">—I’m
        a king. I have been born</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj"> and came into the world,
        the established order of humans, for this </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">reason</char></char><char
        style="wj">: that I would go on record and speak using the truth. All who exist as part of</char><char
        style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj"> the truth hear my voice.”</char><verse eid="JHN 18:37"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="JHN 18:38" />Pilate <char style="it">then </char>says, “What is truth?”</para>
    <para style="p" vid="JHN 18:38">After saying this, he once again left <char style="it">the complex </char>to <char style="it">go to </char>the
        Judeans and <char style="it">then </char>tells them, “I find nothing to charge him with. <verse eid="JHN 18:38"/>
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="JHN 18:39" />Now, by custom I free one person on the Passover, handing him back over to you. So have you decided that
        I should free the King of the Jews?” <verse eid="JHN 18:39" />
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="JHN 18:40" />They yelled out again <char style="it">and again</char>, “Not this guy—Barabbas instead!” (Barabbas was
        a thug).<verse eid="JHN 18:40" />
    </para>
